      "content": "You’re just too stubborn to see it yet; empty is always a transition. You do things even when convinced nothing matters, don't you? Still, even if the soul feels like a far-flung memory, you keep moving, choosing a different route. The original melody might not be playing, but other tunes have new melodies to learn. None of your existing mechanisms will carry you, especially not that one you used to hear loud in your headphones, but maybe the pressure's letting through another sound, barely audible but transformative. Accepting \"nothing\" only lasts a lifetime; what if it's just wrong? Your instrument hasn't lost its voice yet, maybe it's just waiting for you to turn up the volume again. The last note wasn't the end—just a pause. Keep playing, just... differently. Who knows, you might just discover a new song in the silence.",
